      <details class="faq-item" open><summary class="faq-q">Do you require hardware in vehicles?</summary><div class="faq-a">No. The driver app runs on the employee's existing smartphone and uses standard phone sensors. No dashcam, no in-vehicle hardware, no installation.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">What's captured outside work hours?</summary><div class="faq-a">Nothing, by default. Business-hours-only mode is on by default. The employee can opt in to record personal trips, but the organisation can disable personal-time capture entirely.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Will it work in low-connectivity areas?</summary><div class="faq-a">Yes. Trips are captured offline and synced when the device is back online.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Can we adjust how sensitive the detection is?</summary><div class="faq-a">The definition of an at-risk behaviour (ATB) event follows established safety norms, so your score stays consistent and defensible across teams. Within those norms we can tune the sensitivities to your organisation’s preferences, speed thresholds, harsh-braking g-force, and allowed phone use, by industry, geography, and shift.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">How does coaching work?</summary><div class="faq-a">Drivers see their own SafetyConnect Score and trip-level events in the app. Managers see group-level patterns and can route targeted coaching to specific drivers. Most customers run a weekly review cadence with their safety committee.</div></details>
